%0ADear%20Congressperson,%0A%0AThe%20President%20has%20recently%20asked%20Congress%20for%20authorization%20to%20take%20military%20action%20against%20the%20government%20of%20Syria;%20the%20President%20has%20drawn%20a%20red%20line%20that%20he%20alleges%20was%20crossed%20by%20the%20Syrian%20government's%20use%20of%20chemical%20weapons.%20While%20following%20the%20U.S.%20rule%20of%20law%20seeking%20congressional%20authority%20for%20using%20military%20force%20is%20the%20proper%20thing%20to%20do,%20intervening%20in%20Syria%20is%20absolutely%20not.%0A%0AThere%20are%20many%20reasons%20why%20a%20military%20strike%20on%20Syria%20by%20the%20United%20States%20borders%20on%20insanity:%0A*%20An%20attack%20on%20Syria%20does%20not%20benefit%20or%20further%20U.S.%20interests.%0A*%20The%20federal%20government%20is%20already%20over%20$16%20trillion%20in%20debt%20and%20any%20military%20actionwould%20only%20add%20to%20that%20enormous%20debt.%0A*%20A%20strike%20against%20Syria%20could%20very%20well%20be%20a%20precursor%20to%20conflict%20on%20a%20much%20larger%20scale.%0A*%20The%20U.S.%20has%20neither%20the%20authority%20nor%20the%20responsibility%20to%20be%20the%20Policeman%20of%20the%20World.%0A*%20Over%20100,000%20Syrians%20have%20died%20so%20far%20in%20this%20conflict,%20which%20encompasses%20both%20pro%20and%20anti%20government%20factions;%20a%20strike%20on%20Syria%20would%20only%20make%20a%20bad%20humanitarian%20crisis%20worse.%0A*%20The%20very%20terrorists%20that%20we%20have%20been%20fighting%20for%20many%20years%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20benefit%20the%20most%20by%20U.S.%20intervention%20in%20Syria.%0A*%20The%20U.S.%20will%20suffer%20irreparable%20harm%20to%20its%20interests%20and%20credibility%20if%20it%20is%20learned%20that%20the%20Syrian%20government%20were%20not%20behind%20these%20chemical%20attacks.%20Iraq%20is%20still%20fresh%20in%20the%20world's%20memory.%0A%0ABut,%20I%20expect%20that%20I%20am%20not%20telling%20you%20nothing%20that%20you%20don't%20already%20know.%20The%20question%20is:%20What%20are%20you%20going%20to%20do?%20Are%20you%20going%20to%20side%20with%20the%20bankers,%20the%20military/security%20complex,and%20AIPAC,%20or%20are%20you%20going%20to%20side%20with%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20American%20People?%0A%0AChoose%20carefully,%20because%20here%20is%20the%20red%20line%20I%20am%20drawing%20for%20you:%20If%20you%20vote%20for%20the%20U.S.%20to%20intervene%20in%20Syria,%20it%20is%20evident%20that%20you%20are%20neither%20deserving%20or%20qualified%20to%20hold%20public%20office,%20and%20I%20will%20use%20whatever%20legal%20means%20at%20my%20disposal%20to%20insure%20that%20this%20will%20be%20your%20last%20term.%0A%0A
